00:58.658 --> 01:02.160
But these records that we've
uncovered don't tell the story.

01:02.162 --> 01:03.628
They tell pieces of it.

01:03.630 --> 01:09.700
They were looking for...
fundamental information

01:09.702 --> 01:14.572
on compounds that were... would
be capable of causing...

01:17.209 --> 01:19.477
changes in behavior,

01:19.479 --> 01:22.346
changes in mental attitude.

01:22.348 --> 01:23.881
<i>Did you ever consider</i>

01:23.883 --> 01:26.217
<i>what would have happened
if any of these substances</i>

01:26.219 --> 01:28.519
<i>were given to, say,
unwitting people?</i>

01:28.521 --> 01:31.155
<i>Testing it out on an
American citizen?</i>

01:32.791 --> 01:34.158
I...

01:38.831 --> 01:44.202
I guess I must seem very,
very cold-blooded about this,

01:44.204 --> 01:48.039
but I don't recall ever having been

01:48.041 --> 01:50.141
very much preoccupied

01:50.143 --> 01:52.376
with that, uh... with that issue.

01:52.378 --> 01:55.313
Thousands of
government-sponsored experiments

01:55.315 --> 01:58.282
did take place at hospitals,
universities,

01:58.284 --> 02:00.585
and military bases
around our nation.

02:00.587 --> 02:04.222
Some were unethical,
not only by today's standards,

02:04.224 --> 02:06.491
but by the standards of the time

02:06.493 --> 02:08.326
in which they were conducted.

02:08.328 --> 02:10.761
Between the injection and the effects,

02:10.763 --> 02:14.599
the patient was
transported to whatever

02:14.601 --> 02:16.801
or wherever it is
that DMT leads people.

02:16.803 --> 02:21.305
When the Freedom of Information Act
released a bunch of documents,

02:21.307 --> 02:23.808
you found out that all
these different subjects

02:23.810 --> 02:25.576
that had taken this chemical

02:25.578 --> 02:29.647
all experienced the same
phenomena under the drug.

02:29.649 --> 02:31.716
They experienced something out there

02:31.718 --> 02:34.585
that came to them,
that met them halfway.

02:34.587 --> 02:36.354
But what you can't lose sight of

02:36.356 --> 02:37.622
is what all of this would mean

02:37.624 --> 02:39.891
in terms of individual human beings.

02:39.893 --> 02:41.392
There would be deaths,

02:41.394 --> 02:43.995
there would be long-lasting
and harmful effects.

02:43.997 --> 02:46.531
Everyone who took this chemical saw

02:46.533 --> 02:49.400
and witnessed the same thing,

02:49.402 --> 02:51.202
and they all named it
the same thing,

02:51.204 --> 02:53.404
even though they
were separate subjects.

02:53.406 --> 02:55.273
What'd they, uh...
What'd they name it?

02:55.275 --> 02:58.009
Well, that's actually the
name of the chapter.

02:58.011 --> 03:00.745
These entities were kind
of malignant and threatening.

03:00.747 --> 03:02.647
And, actually, a handful
of the volunteers

03:02.649 --> 03:06.184
had traumatic and terrible
encounters with these entities.

03:06.186 --> 03:08.419
Nobody should have
to go through this.

03:08.421 --> 03:12.423
The United States of America
offers a sincere apology

03:12.425 --> 03:14.192
to those of our citizens

03:14.194 --> 03:17.161
who were subjected
to these experiments,

03:17.163 --> 03:19.463
to their families,
and to their communities.

03:19.465 --> 03:22.633
It's something that
I think the general public

03:22.635 --> 03:24.669
has no idea that
our government was doing

03:24.671 --> 03:27.505
and could really open up some...
some eyes.

03:27.507 --> 03:31.442
And would you ever, uh... Would
you ever try the chemical?

03:31.444 --> 03:33.644
Uh, that's a big question, isn't it?

03:33.646 --> 03:35.580
That's the million dollar question.

03:42.854 --> 03:45.189
James Hirsch was a
close friend of mine.

03:45.191 --> 03:47.825
We graduated together
from Atticus University.

03:47.827 --> 03:49.894
We both took
writing courses together,

03:49.896 --> 03:53.297
and we'd often work
on stories late into the night.

03:53.299 --> 03:55.333
We wasted countless hours
at the bar

03:55.335 --> 03:58.135
arguing about
political philosophy and movies.

03:58.137 --> 04:03.107
But four years later,
my friend James went missing.

04:07.312 --> 04:08.713
All right, it's on.

04:08.715 --> 04:11.015
Now what do you want
me to do with it?

04:11.017 --> 04:13.017
Just, um...

04:13.019 --> 04:15.620
I don't trust myself to take accurate
notes while I'm on the chemical,

04:15.622 --> 04:19.357
