I'm surprised
you're not more concerned.

50:48.078 --> 50:48.890
I mean, who knows?

50:48.916 --> 50:51.146
This shit could probably
kill you, too, Thomas.

50:51.148 --> 50:53.081
Oh, people are afraid of death

50:53.083 --> 50:54.983
just because death
is so fucking ordinary.

50:54.985 --> 50:56.985
It happens all the time.

50:56.987 --> 50:58.653
No, not like this.

50:58.655 --> 51:00.355
What about Callie?

51:00.357 --> 51:03.658
How did she get her hands
on this... this chemical formula?

51:03.660 --> 51:06.061
We didn't talk much.
She didn't talk much.

51:06.063 --> 51:07.429
You don't ask questions like that.

51:07.431 --> 51:08.797
It's bad etiquette, you know.

51:08.799 --> 51:10.165
It makes them squirrelly.

51:10.167 --> 51:11.266
Would you know where she lives?

51:11.268 --> 51:12.434
Maybe we can go there and check.

51:12.436 --> 51:13.968
Yeah, sure.
She lives in, uh,

51:13.970 --> 51:16.771
one of these McMansions
she bought outside of Reno.

51:16.773 --> 51:17.972
It was in an empty suburb.

51:17.974 --> 51:19.274
She got it when the market tanked.

51:19.276 --> 51:23.411
We used to go there
and smoke marijuana.

51:31.120 --> 51:32.120
Aah!

51:32.122 --> 51:33.455
Oh, my God!

51:46.236 --> 51:47.735
Are you okay?

51:49.272 --> 51:51.439
Thomas!
Are you okay?

51:51.441 --> 51:54.175
Talk to me!
Oh, fuck.

51:55.479 --> 51:57.912
Oh, my head!
God damn it!

51:57.914 --> 51:59.280
Shit.

51:59.282 --> 52:00.348
Shit.

52:00.350 --> 52:01.916
<i>♪ Someone</i>

52:01.918 --> 52:04.953
<i>♪ And you got someone</i>

52:04.955 --> 52:06.187
<i>♪ Someone</i>

52:06.189 --> 52:09.624
<i>♪ And you got someone</i>

52:09.626 --> 52:11.593
<i>♪ Someone</i>

52:15.064 --> 52:16.364
What happened to you?

52:16.366 --> 52:19.501
I don't know.
I blacked out.

52:19.503 --> 52:23.138
I heard chattering
and then blackness.

52:29.812 --> 52:31.112
Ow, shit!

52:31.114 --> 52:32.380
Thomas?

52:32.382 --> 52:34.215
Ohh!

52:34.217 --> 52:35.583
Are you okay?

52:37.286 --> 52:41.422
The chemical is like a catalyst.

52:41.424 --> 52:44.926
It...
It turns your mind into a receiver.

52:44.928 --> 52:46.694
It lets them in.

52:46.696 --> 52:48.296
How do you know that?

52:49.598 --> 52:52.834
I don't.
It's just a feeling.

52:57.139 --> 52:59.307
Well, I want to find out
who's behind this.

52:59.309 --> 53:02.844
Well, you're in luck, because I
think it wants to find us, too.

53:02.846 --> 53:03.945
You stay there.

53:03.947 --> 53:04.946
Take this with you.

53:04.948 --> 53:06.548
Keep it on channel two.

53:06.550 --> 53:07.882
Stay sharp.

53:09.385 --> 53:11.753
Radio check.

53:13.122 --> 53:14.422
Check.

53:14.424 --> 53:15.924
The button's on the side.

53:16.926 --> 53:18.126
Check.

53:18.128 --> 53:19.494
Check.

53:24.833 --> 53:28.036
Have you
ever read any H.P. Lovecraft?

53:28.038 --> 53:29.504
No.

53:29.506 --> 53:32.740
Wrote a story in about
1930-something or other

53:32.742 --> 53:36.010
was about a scientist who
created an electronic device,

53:36.012 --> 53:38.112
a giant tuning fork.

53:38.114 --> 53:41.349
It emitted
a resonance wave that, um...

53:41.351 --> 53:43.818
It stimulated anybody
who was nearby,

53:43.820 --> 53:47.589
their pineal gland,
allowing them to experience

53:47.591 --> 53:52.493
planes of existence outside the
scope of accepted reality.

53:52.495 --> 53:54.295
He would see incredible,

53:54.297 --> 53:57.899
sometimes horrible things,
these entities.

53:59.268 --> 54:01.769
He kept turning it up
higher and higher,

54:01.771 --> 54:05.173
'cause he was really getting
off on seeing this shit,

54:05.175 --> 54:08.109
but it was too late when he realized

54:08.111 --> 54:10.945
that the entities,

54:10.947 --> 54:13.348
they could see him, too.

54:13.350 --> 54:16.884
You know, that's a really fucked-up
story to be telling me now.

54:28.864 --> 54:30.331
Thomas, it...

54:30.333 --> 54:33.635
It looks like someone's been here.

54:46.181 --> 54:49.784
Are you sure she lived
here, like, ate and slept?

54:49.786 --> 54:51.486
She definitely was here.

54:51.488 --> 54:53.921
How much sleeping she did,
I couldn't tell you.

54:55.791 --> 54:57.625
There's a surveillance camera.

54:59.162 --> 55:00.595
Thomas, can you hear me?

55:00.597 --> 55:01.996
I'm getting static.

55:05.301 --> 55:07.302
What am I looking for?

55:07.304 --> 55:10.204
Should be a basement door
around the kitchen someplace,

55:10.206 --> 55:13.408
because anything she's making
is going to be below ground.

55:13.410 --> 55:14.909
Keeps the feds and
local law enforcement

55:14.911 --> 55:17.945
from using thermal imaging
to discover anything.

55:36.231 --> 55:37.999
I got it.

56:33.055 --> 56:36.824
Callie keeps parts of the
human brain down here.

56:36.826 --> 56:38.960
What does that mean?

56:38.962 --> 56:42.997
It means she took at least part of
the chemical from the human brain.

56:42.999 --> 56:45.767
Well, whatever floats
your boat, right?

56:45.769 --> 56:48.836
Can we go?
It's cold out here.

56:56.945 --> 57:00.014
She found Chamber 5.

57:00.016 --> 57:02.316
It's in the Black Rock Desert.

57:02.318 --> 57:03.351
What?

57:03.353 --> 57:05.052
Callie.
She found Chamber 5.

57:05.054 --> 57:07.522
It's where they did the
original CIA experiments.

57:07.524 --> 57:10.057
Dr. Kessel, MK-ULTRA?

57:10.059 --> 57:11.726
Can we go already?

57:11.728 --> 57:15.062
It's 2:45 in the morning,
and my eyes are bleeding.

57:27.242 --> 57:29.010
The time is 5:13 P.M.,

57:29.012 --> 57:33.281
administering 200 milligrams
of pure Dimethyltryptamine

57:33.283 --> 57:35.950
extracted from the primary source.

57:40.522 --> 57:43.191
N1.

57:43.193 --> 57:45.626
N2.

57:47.262 --> 57:50.998
H2.

57:51.000 --> 57:53.901
O7.

57:53.903 --> 57:59.407
"N1-N2-H2...
- C11.

57:59.409 --> 58:02.143
O7-C11"?

58:05.047 --> 58:07.248
Nitrogen, hydrogen...

58:09.017 --> 58:11.719
oxygen, carbon.

58:13.555 --> 58:16.757
Oh, my God.

58:16.759 --> 58:21.929
Uh, the CIA didn't come up
with the formula.

58:21.931 --> 58:23.865
They did.

58:23.867 --> 58:26.834
Oh, my God.
You were right.

58:26.836 --> 58:29.604
The chemical doesn't
make you hallucinate.

58:29.606 --> 58:32.373
It turns your brain into a receiver

58:32.375 --> 58:34.141
so they could come through.

58:36.311 --> 58:37.712
Shit.

59:45.581 --> 59:49.617
Thomas, I'm looking at
the video surveillance footage.

01:00:03.465 --> 01:00:05.766
It looks like Callie.

01:00:07.469 --> 01:00:09.070
It looks like...

01:00:10.138 --> 01:00:13.107
Callie walked down to the basement.

01:00:13.909 --> 01:00:17.011
Thomas, are you there?

01:00:17.013 --> 01:00:19.880
I can see it on the footage.

01:00:19.882 --> 01:00:21.782
It's by the stairs.

01:00:37.566 --> 01:00:40.234
Eight minutes ago.

01:01:06.395 --> 01:01:07.962
Callie?

01:01:14.369 --> 01:01:15.903
Callie?

01:01:21.243 --> 01:01:23.110
Callie, is that you?

01:01:28.083 --> 01:01:29.817
Callie?

01:02:10.093 --> 01:02:13.160
Aah! Aah!

01:02:13.162 --> 01:02:14.729
Aah!

01:02:16.733 --> 01:02:18.299
Aah!

01:02:18.301 --> 01:02:20.234
Help me!

01:02:28.877 --> 01:02:31.412
Shit! Shit! Fuck!

01:02:33.648 --> 01:02:35.082
Ohh!
Aah!

01:02:35.084 --> 01:02:37.918
Well, Jesus, Anne!
You scared me!

01:02:50.532 --> 01:02:52.399
There's only one option.

01:02:52.401 --> 01:02:54.068
What is that, dear Anne?

01:02:54.070 --> 01:02:56.971
Into the desert, Chamber 5.

01:02:59.274 --> 01:03:00.875
No shit.

01:03:10.986 --> 01:03:12.586
This is the heart of it.

01:03:12.588 --> 01:03:14.155
Everything circles around here.

01:03:14.157 --> 01:03:16.257
I've seen things
in every single place

01:03:16.259 --> 01:03:17.892
before either of us
took the chemical.

01:03:17.894 --> 01:03:21.796
James's cabin, Callie's
house, the desert.

01:03:21.798 --> 01:03:25.866
This is where we need to go if
we want to stop the signal.

01:03:25.868 --> 01:03:29.036
This chemical is creating
more receivers,

01:03:29.038 --> 01:03:32.106
more hosts to wear,
more ways to spread.

01:03:32.108 --> 01:03:34.141
We've been fucked with enough

01:03:34.143 --> 01:03:37.011
by this horrible hydra
of a research project.

01:03:37.013 --> 01:03:38.913
You don't scare too
easily, do you, Anne?

01:03:38.915 --> 01:03:41.348
This shit terrifies
the fuck out of me.

01:03:41.350 --> 01:03:43.450
Well, I'm more scared of
what it will do to me

01:03:43.452 --> 01:03:45.252
if I try to run

01:03:45.254 --> 01:03:49.056
and they all catch up with us.

01:03:49.058 --> 01:03:50.958
What if it doesn't follow us?

01:03:50.960 --> 01:03:53.928
Do you want to bet
your life on that?

01:03:59.100 --> 01:04:01.202
Anne, I never gave you the drug.

01:04:03.138 --> 01:04:04.972
What?

01:04:04.974 --> 01:04:07.041
I was fucking with you.

01:04:07.043 --> 01:04:09.009
You lied to me to get your story,

01:04:09.011 --> 01:04:12.880
so I returned the favor
and I lied to you.

01:04:12.882 --> 01:04:17.451
There wasn't anything in that
whiskey, no... no DMT 19.

01:04:17.453 --> 01:04:19.253
You're lying.
No, I'm not lying.

01:04:19.255 --> 01:04:21.121
You can walk away clean, Anne.

01:04:21.123 --> 01:04:22.423
What will I do when it
catches up with me then?

01:04:22.425 --> 01:04:23.490
Then what?

01:04:23.492 --> 01:04:26.026
The point is, you don't
have to do this.

01:04:26.028 --> 01:04:27.628
No, you're wrong.

01:04:27.630 --> 01:04:30.231
James's friend, Renny,
didn't take the drug.

01:04:30.233 --> 01:04:31.632
It was only a matter of days.

01:04:34.302 --> 01:04:35.402
Anne...

01:04:38.006 --> 01:04:40.441
take your chances.

01:04:40.443 --> 01:04:42.610
Isn't that what I'm doing?

01:05:07.335 --> 01:05:08.836
Ow!

01:05:08.838 --> 01:05:10.371
What?

01:05:10.373 --> 01:05:11.639
Shocked me.

01:05:13.074 --> 01:05:14.475
Static electricity?

01:05:14.477 --> 01:05:15.976
No, no, no, her brain,

01:05:15.978 --> 01:05:18.078
it's still giving off an
electromagnet charge.

01:05:18.080 --> 01:05:19.780
No, no. It's a corpse.

01:05:19.782 --> 01:05:22.216
I know it's a corpse, Doctor.
It still shocked me.

01:05:38.701 --> 01:05:40.167
You seeing this?

01:05:40.169 --> 01:05:43.037
There's still activity in the brain?

01:05:44.372 --> 01:05:47.741
This is something stronger
than normal brain activity.

01:05:47.743 --> 01:05:51.979
State of high alertness, beta
waves range max at 40 hertz.

01:05:51.981 --> 01:05:54.048
This is going up to 135.

01:05:54.050 --> 01:05:55.316
That's strong...

01:06:12.334 --> 01:06:14.702
I think we can walk from here.

01:06:16.838 --> 01:06:18.639
You okay?

01:06:21.576 --> 01:06:24.378
Thomas, you're bleeding again.

01:06:26.382 --> 01:06:27.681
I'm fine.

01:06:27.683 --> 01:06:29.817
You know, we don't have to do this.

01:06:29.819 --> 01:06:31.318
I can take you to a hospital.

01:06:31.320 --> 01:06:34.188
Hey, you said yourself
it'll be waiting for us.

01:06:34.190 --> 01:06:36.557
Let's not disappoint.

01:06:41.229 --> 01:06:43.497
Every now and then,
you run up into a night

01:06:43.499 --> 01:06:47.201
that's a stone-ass bummer
from start to finish.

01:06:47.203 --> 01:06:50.437
On nights like those, if you
know what's good for you,

01:06:50.439 --> 01:06:54.675
you hunker down and you hide.

01:06:58.080 --> 01:07:01.048
This is not one of those nights.

01:07:09.758 --> 01:07:11.592
Tell you what.

01:07:11.594 --> 01:07:13.427
We take this gas can,

01:07:13.429 --> 01:07:16.563
and we torch
whatever we find inside.

01:07:18.099 --> 01:07:20.267
Lead on, Anne.

01:07:44.459 --> 01:07:47.261
This must be where they're
broadcasting from.

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:54.001
There she blows!

01:07:54.003 --> 01:07:56.336
Hump like a snow hill.

01:07:56.338 --> 01:07:58.472
This is an old fallout shelter.

01:07:58.474 --> 01:08:00.908
Well, you gotta give
those government boys credit

01:08:00.910 --> 01:08:02.676
for efficient repurposing.

01:08:27.902 --> 01:08:30.104
After you.

01:08:50.125 --> 01:08:52.826
Well, this is it.

01:08:52.828 --> 01:08:54.694
It's Chamber 5.

01:09:19.053 --> 01:09:21.388
They just left it like this.

01:09:36.304 --> 01:09:38.337
Thomas, put the drugs down.

01:09:51.252 --> 01:09:52.719
You know what that's for, don't you?

01:09:52.720 --> 01:09:53.819
No.

01:09:53.822 --> 01:09:56.423
Medical doctors used
to tie people down to that

01:09:56.425 --> 01:10:00.327
and fill them full of exotic drugs.

01:10:00.329 --> 01:10:02.429
Now, that's entertainment.

01:10:04.365 --> 01:10:05.966
How do you know that?

01:10:59.153 --> 01:11:00.420
What is that?

01:11:00.422 --> 01:11:02.356
Fuck if I know.

01:11:31.119 --> 01:11:33.553
I can't see anything.

01:11:33.555 --> 01:11:34.755
Aah! Oh!

01:11:34.757 --> 01:11:35.756
Oh, my God!

01:11:37.659 --> 01:11:39.359
What is it?

01:11:39.361 --> 01:11:41.962
Thomas, there's something
alive in here!

01:11:47.536 --> 01:11:49.771
This is the transmitter.

01:11:50.773 --> 01:11:54.074
This is the source. We...
We need to burn this thing.

01:11:54.076 --> 01:11:55.609
Where did we put the gas?

01:11:55.611 --> 01:11:57.544
They wanted us to come here!

01:11:57.546 --> 01:11:58.912
Thomas, where the fuck...

01:12:05.020 --> 01:12:06.420
There's something...

01:12:06.422 --> 01:12:07.954
There's something
coming down the hall!

01:12:07.956 --> 01:12:09.623
Thomas, there's something
coming down the hall!

01:12:09.625 --> 01:12:12.526
Close the fucking door!

01:12:14.630 --> 01:12:16.129
They're coming for us.
They're coming for us.

01:12:16.131 --> 01:12:17.964
My God, they're coming for us.

01:12:17.966 --> 01:12:19.566
That's it. We're dead.

01:12:23.238 --> 01:12:25.038
Ohh!

01:12:28.076 --> 01:12:29.609
Oh, fuck.

01:12:34.882 --> 01:12:36.683
Here, you fucks.

01:12:36.685 --> 01:12:38.985
No, no, no, no!
Sorry, Anne.

01:12:38.987 --> 01:12:40.987
Aah!

01:13:03.244 --> 01:13:04.745
Thomas!

01:13:05.847 --> 01:13:07.481
Damn you!

01:14:04.506 --> 01:14:08.008
Please... come... back.

01:14:08.010 --> 01:14:11.978
Please... come... back.

01:14:11.980 --> 01:14:15.816
Please... come... back.

01:14:31.999 --> 01:14:34.201
Aah!

01:14:39.174 --> 01:14:43.243
Please... come... back.

01:14:43.245 --> 01:14:46.680
Please... come... back.

01:14:47.482 --> 01:14:51.551
Please... come... back.

01:14:51.553 --> 01:14:55.489
Please... come... back.

01:14:55.491 --> 01:14:59.025
Please... come... back.

01:15:02.263 --> 01:15:05.131
Please... come... back.

01:15:05.133 --> 01:15:07.167
Come... back.

01:15:07.169 --> 01:15:09.402
Come... back.

01:15:10.506 --> 01:15:12.372
Aah!

01:15:12.374 --> 01:15:14.474
No!

01:15:14.476 --> 01:15:16.076
Aah!

01:15:19.248 --> 01:15:21.114
No!

01:16:18.105 --> 01:16:19.973
No.

01:16:22.843 --> 01:16:25.145
No. No.

01:16:26.480 --> 01:16:29.249
James? No.

01:16:31.252 --> 01:16:33.753
No.

01:18:49.257 --> 01:18:50.590
Thank God!

01:18:50.592 --> 01:18:53.193
I never thought I'd be
so happy to see you.

01:18:53.195 --> 01:18:55.061
Just so damn glad you're safe.

01:18:55.063 --> 01:18:56.796
You scared the shit out of me.

01:18:58.400 --> 01:18:59.899
How you feeling?

01:18:59.901 --> 01:19:01.935
Um, I'm surviving.

01:19:08.943 --> 01:19:11.044
Do you think they'll
charge me with anything?

01:19:11.046 --> 01:19:13.213
Rising Journal will
take care of any legal fees.

01:19:13.215 --> 01:19:15.482
I think they'll just
want to keep you

01:19:15.484 --> 01:19:16.716
a little while for questions

01:19:16.718 --> 01:19:18.785
while they try to sort things out.

01:19:18.787 --> 01:19:21.254
There's gonna be years of questions.

01:19:24.892 --> 01:19:28.595
Video forensics company
sent back your U-matic tape.

01:19:28.597 --> 01:19:31.898
They were able to pull
additional footage from the end.

01:19:31.900 --> 01:19:34.267
Well, what else is on that tape?

01:19:34.269 --> 01:19:38.004
Let's... Let's not
worry about that now.

01:19:39.707 --> 01:19:43.076
The things I saw, I can't...

01:19:43.078 --> 01:19:47.814
I found James's remains,
Olivia, in Chamber 5.

01:19:47.816 --> 01:19:50.784
I... I... It was like he was
watching me this whole time.

01:19:50.786 --> 01:19:52.685
It was wearing him.

01:19:52.687 --> 01:19:54.287
Who?

01:19:54.289 --> 01:19:56.623
It wasn't the drug that killed him.

01:19:56.625 --> 01:19:59.826
It is a chemical catalyst
that turns the brain

01:19:59.828 --> 01:20:02.061
into some sort of receiver
and... and...

01:20:02.063 --> 01:20:04.097
so they could come through.

01:20:04.099 --> 01:20:10.036
Okay. I'm not saying this, but
you know what they'll say.

01:20:11.338 --> 01:20:12.906
They know the truth.

01:20:12.908 --> 01:20:15.241
I... I really wish I didn't.

01:20:17.444 --> 01:20:19.546
Can I ask you something?

01:20:19.548 --> 01:20:21.514
Sure.

01:20:21.516 --> 01:20:26.085
You're 100% certain that Blackburn
didn't put anything in your drink?

01:20:27.154 --> 01:20:28.888
Yeah. Yeah, I'm sure.

01:20:28.890 --> 01:20:30.990
But how do you know for sure?

01:20:30.992 --> 01:20:32.458
He wouldn't.

01:20:32.460 --> 01:20:33.927
He has no reason to.

01:20:33.929 --> 01:20:35.895
Well, I hope you're right.

01:20:37.898 --> 01:20:41.901
'Cause you just never know what's
really going on in someone's head.

01:20:43.470 --> 01:20:45.138
Yeah, you're right.

01:20:47.875 --> 01:20:50.877
You never found
Renny Seegan, did you?

01:20:53.280 --> 01:20:54.247
No.

01:20:54.249 --> 01:20:56.850
And he never took the drug, right?

01:20:59.386 --> 01:21:03.323
No. I...
You're gonna be okay.

01:21:09.431 --> 01:21:10.630
No.

01:21:10.632 --> 01:21:12.699
No, no, no.

01:21:12.701 --> 01:21:14.033
What is that sound?

01:21:15.470 --> 01:21:17.136
No, no, no. No, no.

01:21:17.138 --> 01:21:18.304
Help!

01:21:18.306 --> 01:21:20.740
No! No!

